title: Donkey Logo Needed for Trucking Company
description:
Hello! We're a SAAS company serving the North American trucking industry.
Our demographic is American and Mexican truck drivers, mostly male and ranging in 35-55 years in age, high school level education, family-oriented, old-school humor and personalities.
other_notes:
Hello! Thank you for your interest in this logo project.
Our competition is full of very dry, brandless, product-focussed companies.
Our product is an ELD subscription, it's a mandatory electronic logging device for drivers to track their hours of work. No drivers want to use this, but it is required by law. It’s like a bluetooth timecard at work to make sure they’re doing what they say they’re doing.
Our goal is to offer the same undesirable product, same features and benefits, and win the market over by having a better-more-human brand, sarcastic and relatable marketing, and actually good customer service.
We'd like our logo to have personality (but not too much), a bit of humor (but not too much), attention-grabbing (but not too much), and be simple to remember.
This is why we’re changing our name from Intelelogs to “Haulin’ Ass ELD”. It’s a wordplay on hauling trailers, "haulin ass" as-in fast, and “ass” because the original trucks used to be donkeys and mules back in the day.
Our logo has to be clean enough to look good as an app icon on a phone, and as a sticker on the side of a big rig truck. Can’t be embarrassing for them to put it on their rig, but noticeable enough to catch someone's eye.
Uploaded are ideas we like for inspiration.

title: ✨Our Business Group is in Need of a Powerful, Yet Simple Logo✨
description:
Paradigm21 is a cluster of various businesses that range from Consulting, Real Estate, Mortgage, Investments, Financing, Marketing, Sales, and beyond.
Paradigm (per us): an example, serving as a model. A framework containing ways of thinking, methodology, drive towards excellence, passion to do things differently, more creatively, and more efficiently. A paradigm shift is needed in any and all businesses we're involved in.
What does 21 stand for in the name? 21 is for when the business(es) were established and they represent the 21st Century as well.
Paradigm (per Merriam-Webster): "Paradigm traces to a Greek verb meaning "to show," and has been used in English to mean "example" or "pattern" since the 15th century. Some debate exists, however, about what kind of example qualifies as a paradigm. Some people say it's a typical example, while others insist it must be an outstanding or perfect example."
LOGO IDEA: We'd like to have a logo that could be interchangeable with many subbrands of this parent entity. A serious and BOLD logo with literal lines, simple enough to be easily used for a favicon. We're not looking for a complex design, rather an impactful and memorable one. See the attached examples, but feel free to bring your own concept to the table. We generally like the idea of a shift... a wheel with arrows pointing in a clockwise direction, representing a continuous growth and co-dependence from the previous process. Check our provided examples.
We appreciate your creative consideration! We promise we will be responsive and provide as much direction as it's needed to allow you creative freedom while creating the vision we have for this important business identity item.
other_notes: Dear designer, please submit only well-thought designs that will initiate collaboration from our team. We don't want to decline anybody's designs, ever! However, we're looking for the best possible representation of our many companies, and what better to represent us than a recognizable logo! Thank you again!

title: 99NONPROFITS WINNER: Minimalistic,  & Creative Logo For Preschool Organizations
description:
WHO WE ARE
Establish early childhood development centres in remote mountain areas of Central Asia.
We are a determined group of supportive individuals who have a passion for improving the Quality of Life of the most vulnerable societies by educating their children and their communities in order that they can look forward to a promising sustainable future.
We went where the road was less travelled. And what a difference it has made after 10 years of being there. The road was less travelled due to political instability that created a lack of access to education for early learners. The large global development organizations were not comfortable going to Tajikistan due to this political strife.
Because of lack of knowledge, nobody realized the depth and breadth of the need to educate the early learners in this country. Our organization saw this need and have since then strived to fulfill this need.
